{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σῑτοποι-ός</b>, ον, ἀνάγκη σ. <br /> the task <b>of grinding and baking</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 362. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>substantive</i>, <b>one that ground the corn in the hand-mill, miller.</b> σ. ἐκ τῶν μυλώνων [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.22; Λαμέδοντι σιτοποιῷ “PCair.Zen.” 4.41 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπίστειλον.. πόθεν δεῖ λαβόντα σῖτον καὶ πόσον δοῦναι Ἀμμωνίῳ τῷ σ. ὅπως ἑτοιμασθῇ σεμίδαλις [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “PMich.Zen.” 28.32 (3rd c.BC)\">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; ἔργον σιτοποιοῦ <b>bake-meats</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.Gen.40.17 \">LXX</a>]; mostly <i>feminine</i>, <b>baking-woman</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.150, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “Characteres” 4.7 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; γυναῖκες σ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.187, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.78 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to ὀψοποιός (a cook), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 517e, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 8.5.3 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; opposed to μάγειρος, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Alexander” 23 (_plural_), compare “Ostr.Bodl.” i 304 (_plural_, 2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9089","accentedUnicode":"σιτοποιός","shortDef":"a baker","mediumDef":"a baker","stepGloss":"a baker","stepTransliteration":"sitopoios","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}